cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.LG 

The paper deals with image segmentation using the watershed transform, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on node weighted graphs, which falls under the category of graph algorithms (cs.GR). The pruning and iterative algorithms used in the proposed method involve data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the limitations of current watershed algorithms and proposes a new approach, which can be considered as a machine learning problem (cs.LG).
